This paper focuses on physical human-robot collaboration and manipulation tasks, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks to predict human intent, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves analyzing motion and force data, which could fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of understanding human behavior and collaboration, which could also fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
